India  leads England by 43 runs after
day two of their second cricket Test at Trent Bridge in
Nottingham.  Rahul Dravid scored 117 as India was bowled out for 288 in
reply to Englandâ€™s first-innings 221. Stuart Broad took 6-48,
claiming a hat trick by getting MS Dhoni,  Harbhajan Singh  and
Praveen Kumar with successive balls in the 87th over.  England then reached 24-1 at stumps with Ian Bell nine not
out and Andrew Strauss scoring six.  England won the opening Test by 196 runs. It can overtake
India at the top of the International Cricket Council rankings
by winning the four-game series by two Tests or more.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
